cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.EC 

This paper deals with the problem of maximizing revenue in selling items to a single buyer, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The paper also involves analyzing the revenue ratios between selling items in a bundle and separately, which can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem (cs.DS) and a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper uses known valuation distributions to solve the problem, which suggests a possible application of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
